            Which of the following are power functions?



f (x) = \dfrac{1}{3}x^4 + 2


g(x) = \dfrac{1}{3x^4}


h(x) = \dfrac{x + 6}{x^3}

        Write each function as a power function in the form y = kx ^p.



f (x) = {12}{x^2}


g(x) = \dfrac{1}{4x}


h(x) = \dfrac{2}{5x^6}

subsection.p:
In general, we have the following behaviors of power functions with integer exponents:







              The graph of
               y=x^\text{(odd positive number)}
              is shown to the right. The long run behavior of such a function is given by
              \begin{align*}
              x^\text{(odd positive number)}\to -\infty\ \amp \text{as}\ x\to -\infty\ ,\ \ \text{and}\\
              x^\text{(odd positive number)}\to \infty\ \amp \text{as}\ x\to \infty.
          \end{align*}
          Examples of such functions are  x,x^3,x^5, etc.

          graphs positive odd powers








                The graph of
                 y=x^\text{even positive number}
                is shown to the right. The long run behavior of such a function is given by
                \begin{align*}
                x^\text{even positive number}\to \infty\ \amp \text{as}\ x\to \pm\infty.
                \end{align*}
                Examples of such functions are  x^2,x^4,x^6, etc.

            graphs positive even powers








                The graph of
                 y=x^\text{odd negative number}
                is shown to the right. The long run behavior of such a function is given by
                \begin{align*}
                    x^\text{odd negative number}\to 0\ \amp \text{as}\ x\to \pm\infty.
                    \end{align*}
                Examples of such functions are  x^{-1},x^{-3},x^{-5}, etc.

            graphs negative odd powers








                The graph of
                 y=x^\text{even negative number}
                is shown to the right. The long run behavior of such a function is given by
                \begin{align*}
                    x^\text{even negative number}\to 0\ \amp \text{as}\ x\to \pm\infty
                    \end{align*}
                Examples of such functions are  x^{-2},x^{-4},x^{-6}, etc.

            graphs negative even powers
